00:14:59,418 --> 00:15:17,555
Here tonight to present this year's Ambassador Award is video game writer and content creator Alana Pierce.

163
00:15:17,555 --> 00:15:22,860
Hello everyone. I struggle to think of a person who is more deserving of receiving this year's

164
00:15:22,860 --> 00:15:25,343
Ambassador Award than my friend Stephen Spock.

165
00:15:32,082 --> 00:15:36,506
This award is for someone who has helped the games industry advance to a better place,

166
00:15:36,506 --> 00:15:41,651
and if I were to give Steve one criticism, it is that he has tirelessly tried so hard

167
00:15:41,651 --> 00:15:46,475
to advance the games industry to a better place that it has probably come at his own

168
00:15:46,475 --> 00:15:46,915
expense.

169
00:15:46,915 --> 00:15:52,521
Steve has effectively dedicated his life to championing video game accessibility, sometimes

170
00:15:52,521 --> 00:15:55,063
even braving the inner workings of Reddit.

171
00:15:56,146 --> 00:16:00,168
Can you imagine telling Reddit you think disabled gamers should be able to play FromSoft games

172
00:16:00,168 --> 00:16:04,310
and coming out of that on the other side filled with good vibes?

173
00:16:04,310 --> 00:16:04,490
No.

174
00:16:04,490 --> 00:16:05,271
No, you can't.

175
00:16:05,271 --> 00:16:10,533
And yet, even though it is undoubtedly hard and taxing, Steve persists where others won't

176
00:16:10,533 --> 00:16:11,834
because Steve is the best of us.

177
00:16:11,834 --> 00:16:14,035
If you don't know Steven Spahn, you're missing out.

178
00:16:14,035 --> 00:16:19,658
Not only because he's one of the funniest people I know, to be clear he paid me to put

179
00:16:19,658 --> 00:16:23,480
that in the script, I'll take the $50 after the award is done, thanks Steve, but he's

180
00:16:23,480 --> 00:16:24,901
also incredibly accomplished.

181
00:16:25,237 --> 00:16:28,620
Steve is the Senior Director of Able Gamers, which is an organization that's dedicated

182
00:16:28,620 --> 00:16:41,713
to improving accessibility in video games, and enabling more people with disabilities

183
00:16:41,713 --> 00:16:42,934
to be able to play video games.

184
00:16:42,934 --> 00:16:48,979
