185
00:16:48,979 --> 00:16:50,781
of a campaign he called Spawn Together.

186
00:16:51,327 --> 00:16:54,069
That's more than most people have accomplished in our entire lifetimes,

187
00:16:54,069 --> 00:16:56,471
and Steve did it to celebrate his own birthday.

188
00:16:56,471 --> 00:17:01,896
Most of us sleep in a little bit longer and order a pizza.

189
00:17:01,896 --> 00:17:04,458
Steve banded together a huge team of people to raise a million dollars,

190
00:17:04,458 --> 00:17:06,780
all in the name of providing gaming peripherals and hardware

191
00:17:06,780 --> 00:17:10,083
to people who may not be able to play games without them.

192
00:17:10,083 --> 00:17:12,304
He also managed to repeatedly murder me in Among Us,

193
00:17:12,304 --> 00:17:15,807
and beat me in Fall Guys repeatedly, probably all in the same day.

194
00:17:15,807 --> 00:17:17,569
Actually, I take back everything that I've said.

195
00:17:17,569 --> 00:17:19,770
Steve is horrible.

196
00:17:19,770 --> 00:17:20,991
Hashtag cancel Steven's phone.

197
00:17:22,462 --> 00:17:24,763
But really, outside of his work directly with AbleGamers,

198
00:17:24,763 --> 00:17:27,004
and his work being the only righteous troll

199
00:17:27,004 --> 00:17:28,785
in the entirety of Twitter.

200
00:17:28,785 --> 00:17:30,787
Steve has also done a tremendous job

201
00:17:30,787 --> 00:17:32,608
of recruiting people outside of the industry

202
00:17:32,608 --> 00:17:34,249
to talk about video game accessibility.

203
00:17:34,249 --> 00:17:36,010
People like Ryan Reynolds and Brie Larson,

204
00:17:36,010 --> 00:17:38,391
some of the biggest streamers and content creators

205
00:17:38,391 --> 00:17:40,052
can't help but be on Steve's side.

206
00:17:40,052 --> 00:17:42,074
And this is supposed to be a speech about his work,

207
00:17:42,074 --> 00:17:43,375
but I can't go on without mentioning

208
00:17:43,375 --> 00:17:46,256
that part of it is because he's so incredibly kind,

209
00:17:46,256 --> 00:17:48,318
engaging, charismatic, and...

210
00:17:49,336 --> 00:17:55,962
Incredibly ridiculously handsome. Okay, now he's just editing the teleprompter. He can't keep getting away with this

211
00:17:55,962 --> 00:18:00,526
I could talk for a really really long time about why I'm honored to call Steve one of my best friends and how I'm so

212
00:18:00,526 --> 00:18:03,608
Proud to have been asked to present him with this year's Ambassador Award

213
00:18:03,608 --> 00:18:11,275
But I'm worried that he has slipped more sly compliments about himself into my script. So that is it for me. Welcome Steve Spahn everybody

214
00:18:37,129 --> 00:18:42,215
She doesn't realize I can't hold that award.

215
00:18:42,215 --> 00:18:54,188
It's an honor and a privilege to share this evening of inscription with you.

216
00:18:54,696 --> 00:18:57,697
Years ago, before my first industry event,

217
00:18:57,697 --> 00:19:00,478
I stayed up all night meticulously writing

218
00:19:00,478 --> 00:19:03,919
the importance of helping people with disabilities.

219
00:19:03,919 --> 00:19:07,540
The very first day, I presented that information

220
00:19:07,540 --> 00:19:10,160
to a lead developer at Rockstar Games.

221
00:19:10,160 --> 00:19:11,541
He ignored me.

222
00:19:11,541 --> 00:19:13,942
Instead, looking right over my wheelchair,

223
00:19:13,942 --> 00:19:16,162
directly at my invisibly disabled,

224
00:19:16,162 --> 00:19:18,643
able gamers partner, Mark Barlet,

225
00:19:18,643 --> 00:19:21,104
then crumpled up the pamphlet,

226
00:19:21,104 --> 00:19:24,125
threw it in the trash, and walked away.

227
00:19:24,125 --> 00:19:24,445
I was devastated.

228
00:19:25,253 --> 00:19:31,037
It was at that moment that I knew there was no seat at the table for someone like me.

229
00:19:31,037 --> 00:19:35,000
So I set out and made my mission to make one.

230
00:19:35,000 --> 00:19:42,185
People tell me I am strong, resilient, inspirational, but I'm here to tell you that I am not.

231
00:19:42,185 --> 00:19:43,446
I am here.

232
00:19:43,446 --> 00:19:49,190
I didn't quit because my options were to be those things or die.

233
00:19:49,190 --> 00:19:50,230
I chose not death.

234
00:19:50,230 --> 00:19:52,832
I didn't choose this life.

235
00:19:53,358 --> 00:19:55,494
but I'm gonna make every second of it count.

236
00:20:16,854 --> 00:20:17,755
It is just impossible.

237
00:20:17,755 --> 00:20:21,858
Do you know how many times as a person with a terminal disease

238
00:20:21,858 --> 00:20:27,241
and as a disabled man as I am that I have been told the words,

239
00:20:27,241 --> 00:20:28,702
it's impossible?

240
00:20:28,702 --> 00:20:30,724
You're never going to live past 10 years old.

241
00:20:30,724 --> 00:20:31,945
It's impossible.

242
00:20:31,945 --> 00:20:34,226
You won't live long enough to see the end of college.

243
00:20:34,226 --> 00:20:35,287
It's impossible.

244
00:20:35,287 --> 00:20:36,828
You're never going to find love.

245
00:20:36,828 --> 00:20:38,609
It's impossible.

246
00:20:38,609 --> 00:20:43,032
You'll never make people care about game accessibility.

247
00:20:43,032 --> 00:20:43,993
It's impossible.

248
00:20:43,993 --> 00:20:46,255
I am here to tell you that not everything is impossible.

249
00:20:58,822 --> 00:21:03,146
One thing that I have learned is if you fight for your limitations,

250
00:21:03,146 --> 00:21:05,007
you will never lose them.

251
00:21:05,007 --> 00:21:08,950
Never limit yourself or allow others to put limitations on you.

